Show HN: tsdocker – run Docker containers on your Tailnet
text:
I wanted a way to spin up Docker containers exposed on Tailscale without running Tailscale in the container itself.

Now that Tailscale supports creating virtual nodes in Go[0], it's possible to create a distinct Tailscale network interface for each container, which is exactly what tsdocker does.

[0] https://tailscale.com/blog/tsnet-virtual-private-services/

Ask HN: Why is SceneKitQLThumbnailExtension using all my RAM?
text:
I've noticed since updating to MacOS Ventura the `SceneKitQLThumbnailExtension` process climbs in RAM usage, up to 20+ GBs until I eventually kill it. Not sure if it's leaking or if it's by design (given I have a lot of headroom).

Is anyone else experiencing this? My hardware: 14" macbook pro, M1 Max, 64GB RAM
